content.p:
Invites Member States to consider ratifying relevant conventions of the International Labour Organization, including the Domestic Workers Convention, 2011 (No. 189), on decent work for domestic workers,
United Nations, Treaty Series, vol. 2955, No. 51379. as well as the Abolition of Forced Labour Convention 1957 (No. 105);
Ibid., vol. 320, No. 4648.

Welcomes the recommendations on strengthening cooperation on missing migrants and providing humanitarian assistance to migrants in distress, set out in the report of the Secretary-General,
A/79/590, annex. pursuant to the Progress Declaration of the first International Migration Review Forum;
Resolution 76/266, annex.
